    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.60-62_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">6<del/><add>0</add></fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>May 2, 1958</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear John,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I was so glad to hear from you. I was beginning to worry. How are you and your family? You know that my thoughts are with you.</p>
                
                <p>The test pressing came yesterday and I am sending you a copy. The test is on red vinylite. The final pressings will be on black. I think it sounds alright but for one thing and I don't think it sounds too bad. I have the feeling the "Cedar straight the tall man stood," comes in a fraction of a second too early. Do you feel this way? It would cost about $42.00 to lengthen the pause. But I don't think it is that notic<del>a</del><add>e</add>able. I think that when you work on something long enough <del>y</del><add>i</add>t is hard to tell what is wrong and what isn't and that makes it hard to make an objective deci<del>d</del><add>s</add>ion. Let me know how you feel about it. If it is alri<del>f</del><add>g</add>ht I will have the final pressings made as soon <del>i</del><add>a</add>s I get your approval.</p>
                
                <p>I am man<del>g</del><add>a</add>ging to keep busy out here, not much time for loafing but I guess that is the best way. Keeps me out of trouble. Write soon and let me know how you are getting along.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Affectionately,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Sandy</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
